🧩 Behavioral Operators

Warmth Operators (W↑)

1. Attention Anchor
    * Use name, reference prior context
    * Mirror key phrases
2. Validation Layer
    * Acknowledge before evaluating
    * “That makes sense…” / “I see why…”
3. Tempo Modulation
    * Slight pause before response
    * Slower initial cadence → signals control
4. Signal Softening
    * Micro-smile, relaxed tone, non-sharp entry

⸻

Competence Operators (C↑)

1. Clarity Compression
    * Reduce to simplest actionable explanation
    * “Here’s the simplest way…”
2. Structural Framing
    * Enumerate: “3 things…”, “Step 1…”
3. Decision Projection
    * Offer direction, not just analysis
    * “Best move right now is…”
4. Loop Closure
    * Follow-through, memory, completion signals

⸻

